title: Reactions Induced in Fe54 with 21-63 MeV Li6 Ions

x4freetext: Reactions Induced in Fe54 with 21-63 MeV Li6 Ions

x4codes.hlp: University of Rochester, Rochester, NY, United States of America
Yale University, New Haven, CT, United States of America

x4freetext: Iron target, electroplated onto
gold foils. Areal density 10.2-10.9 mg/cm2.
Aluminum catcher/degrader foils
interspersed between target foils. The iron was
dissolved from the gold foils with 16M NHO3. The
catcher foils were dissolved in the resulting nitric
acid solution. Calibrated end window proportional
counters were used for all measurements of beta+
radiation. A 3-in.x 3-in. NaI crystal and 512-channel
pulse-height analyzer were used for x-ray
measurement; the efficiency curves of Heath were used
to obtain crystal efficiencies. The Fe55 K x-rays
were counted with a 1-in.-diam by 1/32-in. -thick NaI
crystal having a 3-mil-thick beryllium window. A
geometric factor of 0.30 was calculated for the
system. Corrections were applied for self-absorption
and window absorption.

x4freetext: Estimate of uncertainty on absolute value.
Beam energy as a function of target depth was
calculated using semiempirical ranges of 6Li in
aluminum. These values were adopted from the original
compilation.
Converted from data set p0135 and updated.
